title.narrative: Building Local Capacity (BLC) for Delivery of HIV Services in Southern Africa

description.narrative: (USAID Southern Africa Regional): High background HIV prevalence, along with an unacceptably high rate of new infections, has widespread effects which undermine the ability of all sectors to attain their development objectives in the region. To promote a holistic provision of care, MSH will identify opportunities to integrate treatment and care services into the prevention programs currently being provided to migrants. Key in this activity is close collaboration and related systems strengthening which will enable the HIV Unit in the Southern African Development Community (SADC) to effectively implement its Global Fund grant for addressing HIV in migrant populations. Underpinning all activities is the BLC project's focus on health systems strengthening (HSS) and building capacity of local regional partners. As a key milestone, the BLC project has the target of graduating ten local partners to become direct recipients of USG funds by the end of the project.
